Package org.sbml.jsbml.validator.offline.constraints

Class ValidationConstraint<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.validator.offline.constraints.AbstractConstraint<T>
      • org.sbml.jsbml.validator.offline.constraints.ValidationConstraint<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AnyConstraint<T>

    public class ValidationConstraint<T>
extends AbstractConstraint<T>
    The basic constraint which uses a ValidationFunction object to perform validation.

    Notice that two ValidationConstraint objects are equal if they have the same error Code.

    Since:
    1.2
    Author:
    Roman

      • check

        public boolean check​(ValidationContext context,
                     T t)
        Description copied from interface: AnyConstraint
        Checks if the object conforms to the specific rule in the given context.

        If the rule behaves different for each level/version, the level and version of the context will be used.

        Parameters:
        context - the validation context
        t - the object to validate
        Returns:
        false if the object does not respect the constraint
